	<dd><a name="comment_1851" ></a>
	<p><em><strong>Well-off Graduate</strong> replies:</em> I'd like to defend our student for hanging onto his PC when destitute in all other ways. An old PC is worth next-to-nothing, but its a huge enabling device. Without the Internet, the time and money required to try and find a job, or just day-to-day information or a job multiply hugely. And if it weren't for his PC, we wouldn't have even heard his opinion.<br />When I'm living in a cardboard box, it'll be one near an unsecured wi-fi point, and they'll prise my 3-year old laptop from my dead fingers.</p>
	<small>
	written 25th Apr 2005 <!-- | <a
    href="/abuse/?postid=1435&amp;commentid=1851">abusive?</a>
